# Cursor Rules — Lightweight Astro Header, Sidebar, Footer

## Scope

Build only:

- Header
- Sidebar
- Mobile navigation
- Footer
- Light mode
- Dark mode
- Base responsive layout

Do not build:

- tool forms
- wallet connection
- Solana logic
- API calls
- transaction logic
- dashboards
- React app shell

---

## Core Goal

Create a modern, user-friendly, fully responsive Astro layout shell with almost zero initial JavaScript.

The layout must be:

- extremely lightweight
- modern
- clean
- easy to use
- mobile-first
- SEO-friendly
- accessible
- fast on low-end mobile devices
- excellent for Google PageSpeed

Initial JavaScript should be as close to zero as possible.

If something can be done with Astro, HTML, or CSS, do not use JavaScript.

---

## Stack Rules

Use:

- Astro
- Tailwind CSS
- semantic HTML
- CSS-first behavior
- tiny inline JavaScript only when unavoidable

Do not use:

- React for header/sidebar/footer
- client-side layout hydration
- Ant Design
- Rewind UI package
- dashboard UI kits
- Framer Motion
- animation libraries
- heavy icon libraries
- wallet packages
- Solana packages
- Reown packages

---

## Astro-First Rules

Header, sidebar, mobile navigation, and footer must be Astro components.

Recommended structure:

```txt
src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro

src/components/layout/Header.astro
src/components/layout/Sidebar.astro
src/components/layout/MobileNav.astro
src/components/layout/Footer.astro
src/components/layout/ThemeToggle.astro
src/components/layout/NavGroup.astro
src/components/layout/NavItem.astro
```

Do not convert static layout components into React islands.

Do not hydrate static navigation.

---

## Initial JavaScript Rules

Initial JavaScript must be minimal or zero.

Allowed JavaScript only for:

* dark/light theme persistence
* mobile menu open/close if CSS-only is not practical

Avoid JavaScript for:

* desktop sidebar
* footer
* active link rendering
* hover effects
* dropdown animations
* layout state
* navigation rendering

Prefer:

* Astro-rendered HTML
* CSS media queries
* Tailwind responsive classes
* native HTML behavior where possible

---

## Theme Rules

Support:

* light mode
* dark mode

Use Tailwind `dark:` classes.

Dark mode should work by toggling the `dark` class on `<html>`.

Use a tiny inline head script only to prevent theme flicker and read saved preference.

Theme preference:

* read from `localStorage`
* fallback to system preference
* save user choice to `localStorage`

No theme provider.

No React theme component.

---

## No Animation Rules

Do not add animations.

Do not use:

* Framer Motion
* animation libraries
* page transitions
* animated gradients
* animated backgrounds
* slide animations
* complex hover motion

Allowed:

* instant state changes
* simple color change on hover
* simple border/background change on hover

---

## Header Rules

Header must be:

* Astro-rendered
* lightweight
* modern
* clean
* sticky only if it stays simple and fast
* readable in light and dark mode

Header should include:

* logo
* primary navigation
* theme toggle
* mobile menu button

Header must not include real wallet logic now.

A future wallet button placeholder is allowed only as static HTML.

Header must not import client-only or blockchain packages.

Recommended height:

```txt
64px
```

---

## Sidebar Rules

Desktop sidebar must be:

* Astro-rendered
* lightweight
* modern
* user-friendly
* easy to scan
* grouped by tool category
* visible on desktop
* hidden on mobile
* collapsible on desktop

Sidebar should include:

* category labels
* navigation links
* active state
* hover state
* optional lightweight inline SVG icons
* clear collapse/expand control

Recommended groups:

* Token Creation
* Token Management
* Authority Tools
* Liquidity Tools
* Wallet Tools
* Bundler Tools
* Guides

Avoid:

* nested complex menus
* client-side state
* heavy icon imports
* JavaScript-driven navigation

Sidebar collapse behavior:

* keep interactions instant (no animation)
* prefer CSS-first approach where practical
* if JavaScript is used, keep it tiny and only for toggling collapsed state
* preserve accessibility for keyboard users and screen readers

Recommended width:

```txt
260px
```

---

## Mobile Navigation Rules

Mobile navigation must be:

* very lightweight
* touch-friendly
* readable
* fast
* full responsive
* no horizontal scroll

On mobile:

* hide desktop sidebar
* show menu button in header
* show simple mobile nav panel/menu
* close menu after link click if JavaScript is used

Minimum tap target:

```txt
44px
```

Do not use heavy drawer/sheet libraries.

Do not use animation.

Prefer CSS-first implementation.

---

## Footer Rules

Footer must be:

* Astro-rendered
* static HTML
* lightweight
* modern
* clean
* responsive
* readable in light and dark mode

Footer should include:

* short brand description
* important tool links
* guide links
* trust/safety links
* legal links
* copyright

Avoid:

* oversized footer
* huge link blocks
* decorative clutter
* heavy icons
* JavaScript

---

## Responsive Rules

Use mobile-first design.

Required behavior:

```txt
Mobile:
Header
Mobile Navigation
Main Content
Footer

Desktop:
Header
Sidebar + Main Content
Footer
```

Layout must work on:

* small mobile
* large mobile
* tablet
* laptop
* desktop

No horizontal scroll.

Recommended spacing:

```txt
Mobile padding: 16px
Tablet padding: 24px
Desktop padding: 32px
```

---

## Design Rules

Design must feel:

* modern
* clean
* professional
* calm
* user-friendly
* lightweight
* trustworthy

Avoid:

* crypto casino style
* excessive neon
* heavy gradients
* glassmorphism everywhere
* tiny gray text
* visual clutter
* noisy backgrounds
* oversized decorative elements

Use:

* clear spacing
* readable typography
* subtle borders
* soft surfaces
* simple active states
* one primary accent color
* clean dark mode layers

---

## Accessibility Rules

Use semantic HTML:

* `header`
* `nav`
* `aside`
* `main`
* `footer`

Mobile menu button must include:

* `aria-label`
* `aria-expanded`
* `aria-controls`

Theme toggle must include accessible text or label.

Navigation must be keyboard accessible.

Contrast must be readable in both light and dark mode.

---

## Performance Rules

Must keep PageSpeed impact extremely low.

Do:

* render layout with Astro
* avoid hydration
* avoid large dependencies
* avoid unnecessary JavaScript
* use inline SVG only when needed
* keep DOM clean
* keep CSS practical
* keep mobile simple

Do not:

* import React for layout
* import Solana SDK
* import wallet libraries
* import Reown
* import animation libraries
* import large icon packs globally
* import UI dashboard kits
* use large images in layout
* use video backgrounds
* use animated backgrounds

---

## Acceptance Checklist

This step is complete only when:

* Header is Astro-rendered
* Sidebar is Astro-rendered
* Footer is Astro-rendered
* Mobile navigation is lightweight
* Sidebar is collapsible
* Initial JavaScript is near zero
* No React hydration exists for layout
* No wallet package exists
* No Solana package exists
* No Reown package exists
* No animation library exists
* Light mode works
* Dark mode works
* Mobile layout works
* Desktop layout works
* No horizontal scroll exists
* Navigation is easy to use
* UI is modern and clean
* PageSpeed impact is minimal
* Site remains readable without JavaScript

## Final Rule

If a design choice increases initial JavaScript, dependency size, or mobile weight, reject it.

Choose the lighter, simpler, faster solution.
